 Luis SuarezWelsh star Gareth Bale says the UEFA Champions League means everything to Real Madrid, winner of the first five European Cups and a record 10 overall.
"It's the main priority every year," he told the London Times before Tuesday's semifinal at Manchester City. "It's just in the club's nature, they want to win the European Cup every year. It's instilled in you and you go for it every year.
"It's special to the club. Even when you play on European nights, the atmosphere's that bit better, everyone in the stands is kicking every ball for you. It's always more intense for Champions League games, because it means so much for the club." Read the original story...CommentRecommend (0)Tweet No comments yet.Sign in to leave a comment. Don't have an account? Join NowUsernamePasswordRemember meForgot your password? AUTHORSSoccerAmerica MastheadARCHIVES April 2016 March 2016 February 2016 January 2016 December 2015 November 2015All Archives October 2015 September 2015 August 2015 July 2015 June 2015 May 2015 April 2015 March 2015 February 2015 January 2015FOLLOW SOCCERAMERICAJoinJoin 180K soccer fans for Free SoccerAmerica Membership Follow @socceramericaRecentAround The Net in Soccer World DailyAtletico Madrid, the Leicester of the UCLApril 25, 10:03 p.m.
